				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There really is not too much to talk about here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /> --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT="<img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>If you're in a zone with skeletons, stay with them until they no longer give you experience. Several reasons for this: 1. They never run. 2. You can sell bones to Necromancers (or give them away if you want to start building friendships for later).<br><br>Other helpfull hints:<br>Similar to the hunting skele's for bones... Hunt creatures that have loot you can use. For us casters, killing orc pawns can loot most of a full set of cloth by the time you're finishing 3rd and getting ready for 4th.<br><br>Use the highest damage weapon you can get (usually a 2H blunt for us, but I think a cracked staff is not too bad, and easy to get). Some people say go for low delay to increase your skill, but as a Mage we'll NEVER be all that good at melee, so you want to get those nice one shot 16 damage hits from a 2 handed fine steel great staff <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /> --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT="<img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>If you can find a nice druid or cleric to buff you, you can do these levels in all of 30min <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /> --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT="<img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Getting a hit point buff from a 30+ cleric, or some of the druid's nice skin and regeneration spells can make a HUGE difference. Not to mention out own (and Druid) damage shields. If you do get damage shields, try to look for the faster critters to kill (like wasps, snakes, and wolves) since their hitting you faster will only kill themselves quicker <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /> --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT="<img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Finally, if you are in a zone with creatures that have quests for their loot (I.E. turning in Pixie dusts in Kelethin, or Orc hatchets/belts/etc...) will let you get double experience in a sense <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /> --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT="<img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  The exp from most of these low level quests dies off pretty quick, so use them while you're still low <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /> --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT="<img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>That's about all I can think of for now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /> --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT="<img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Please, everyone else jump in and post any other hints for wee youngsters <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" /> --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT="<img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" />"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Thanks, <p><b>Ommundan Rii</b><br><img src="http://home.cfl.rr.com/exarch/LLRINGS.GIF"><br>Master of the Hunt<br>Magi, Rodcet Nife</p><i></i><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=326327" target="new">Ommundan Rii</a>, <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower" target="new">Arch Convoker and Master of the Hunt</a>, <a href="http://pub145.ezboard.com/bhegemony" target="new">Hegemony</a>, <a href="http://pub59.ezboard.com/bguild75784" target="new">Rodcet Nife</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
