				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">One other recommendation for young lowbie. Rats. Since the new armor quests the rats have gotten new drops besides the regular, ears, whiskers and meat and the occational foot. They have aquired the ability to see, in the guyse of an eye. Eye that goes for 2 gold apiece. Also the tail catches a hefty penny of a whole 1 plat. A nice catch for a youngling. Rats are not an isolated incident although the tail is the highest one ive found that sells for so much.<br><br>Most dropped objects needed for the newbie quests and are not no drop go for about 2 to 4 gold appiece. and if they stack... whoopa mama!<br><br>And I would also recommend doing the newbie armor quests themselves as well. It may be tedious getting all the items but the clothing is much more supperiour to banded or raw silk. Not only is it lighter; it is free. And most important, you get the pride of wearing something that you got for yourself. Through your own toil, determentation and ingeniouity you have gotten yourself a suit of armor and a weapon. And nothing can take that away from you.<br><br>I experienced that with my young dwarven cleric. Got all pieces and the weapon. And I gotta tell you Im so proud im busting my bridges. But then again im NEVER going through that again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" /> --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT="<img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" />"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Stina 1701A<br>-----------<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Server:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Drinal.<br>Kestran Treesnatcher. Rogue.<br>Berglind. Enchanter.<br>Hulda. Cleric.<br>Twitterbug. Paladin.<br>Slumber. Warrior.<br>-----------<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Guild:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Heart of the Hunter.<br>-----------<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Quote of the Week:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD EN